
AUTO INCREMENT -
==================


- Auto Increment is Generally used for Primary Key



CREATE TABLE employees (
employee_id INT AUTO_INCREMENT,
first_name VARCHAR(40),
last_name VARCHAR(40),
hire_date DATE,
PRIMARY KEY (employee_id)
);






A) If we Have a Requirement that the Employee_id Should Start from 1000 so we can use below

ALTER TABLE employees AUTO_INCREMENT = 1000;



B) If we want That Auto_Increment should be done by 2 [First Record is 1001, Second should be 1003, 1005 and so on] 

SET @@auto_increment_increment = 2;











